            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary">
              <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble Ralph</li>
              <li>Modify, adapt, or create derivative works without permission</li>
              <li>Sublicense, sell, or distribute Ralph to third parties</li>
              <li>Use Ralph for any unlawful purpose</li>
              <li>Remove or alter any proprietary notices</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">4. Data Ownership and Privacy</h2>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">4.1 Your Data</h3>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              You retain all rights, title, and interest in your data. Ralph processes your data solely on your infrastructure, and we have no access to, control over, or rights in your data.
            </p>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">4.2 No Data Collection</h3>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We do not collect, store, or process any of your business data. Your data never leaves your controlled environment.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">5. Security and Compliance</h2>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">5.1 Our Security Commitments</h3>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We develop Ralph using industry-leading security practices:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary mb-4">
              <li>Regular security audits and penetration testing</li>
              <li>Secure development lifecycle with code reviews</li>
              <li>Pursuit of SOC 2 Type I and Type II certifications</li>
              <li>Encrypted communications and secure deployment practices</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">5.2 Your Security Responsibilities</h3>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              As the data controller, you are responsible for:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary mb-4">
              <li>Configuring and maintaining security within your deployment environment</li>
              <li>Ensuring compliance with applicable financial and data protection regulations</li>
              <li>Managing user access, permissions, and authentication systems</li>
              <li>Implementing backup, disaster recovery, and business continuity procedures</li>
              <li>Monitoring and auditing system access and usage</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">5.3 Compliance Support</h3>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Ralph is designed to support compliance with various regulatory frameworks including GDPR, CCPA, and financial industry regulations. However, achieving and maintaining compliance is your responsibility as the deploying organization.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">6. Support and Service Levels</h2>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">6.1 Support Services</h3>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              We provide comprehensive support services according to your subscription tier:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary mb-4">
              <li><strong>Technical Support:</strong> Troubleshooting, configuration assistance, and issue resolution</li>
              <li><strong>Security Updates:</strong> Priority patches for security vulnerabilities</li>
              <li><strong>Feature Updates:</strong> Regular enhancements and new functionality</li>
              <li><strong>Documentation:</strong> Comprehensive guides, API documentation, and best practices</li>
              <li><strong>Training:</strong> User onboarding and administrator training resources</li>
              <li><strong>Professional Services:</strong> Custom deployment, integration, and optimization services</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">6.2 Service Level Commitments</h3>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              While Ralph operates on your infrastructure, we commit to:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary mb-4">
              <li>Respond to critical support requests within the timeframes specified in your service agreement</li>
              <li>Provide advance notice of significant updates or changes</li>
              <li>Maintain comprehensive documentation and knowledge base</li>
              <li>Offer escalation paths for urgent technical issues</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">6.3 Update Management</h3>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              You maintain complete control over update deployment:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary">
              <li>All updates are tested and validated before release</li>
              <li>You choose when and how to apply updates to your environment</li>
              <li>Rollback procedures are available for all updates</li>
              <li>Critical security updates are clearly identified and prioritized</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">7. Fees and Payment</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Fees are determined by your subscription agreement and may include:
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-2 ml-6 text-secondary">
              <li>Initial setup and deployment fees</li>
              <li>Annual or monthly subscription fees</li>
              <li>Additional fees for premium features or support</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-4">
              Payment terms are specified in your subscription agreement.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">8. Intellectual Property</h2>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Ralph and all associated intellectual property rights remain the exclusive property of Beneficious. These Terms do not grant you any rights to our trademarks, trade names, or other brand features.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary mb-3 pb-2 border-b border-neutral-700">9. Warranties and Service Guarantees</h2>
            <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-primary mb-2 mt-6">9.1 Service Warranty</h3>
            <p class="text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-4">
